article.headline: Idaho 74, S. Dakota St. 66
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- Keoni Watson scored 26 points and Michael Crowell added 14 to lead Idaho to a 74-66 win over South Dakota State Thursday. The Vandals (1-1) shot 54 percent from the field in the second half to erase a 32-29 halftime deficit. Idaho made 10 of 27 3-point attempts. Watson was 4-for-7 from 3-point range and Crowell went 4-for-6. SDSU (0-4) led at half despite shooting only 41 percent from the field. Mackenzie Casey scored a career-high 21 points for the Jackrabbits. Matt Cadwell added 20 points and five rebounds.
